getLength().Description: The number of DOMStrings in the list. The range of valid child node indices is 0 to length-1 inclusive.

Returns: The DOMString at the indexth position in the DOMStringList, or null if that is not a valid index.
item(int).Description: Returns the indexth item in the collection. If index is greater than or equal to the number of DOMStrings in the list, this returns null.

Returns: true if the string has been found, false otherwise.
Parameters: String: The string to look for.
contains(java.lang.String).Description: Test if a string is part of this DOMStringList.
